            <p class="ceg-b32"><strong>How to find a man&rsquo;s glove size?</strong> To find your glove size, measure your dominant hand (the hand you write with) using a tape measure. Here are step-by-step instructions courtesy of Isotoner:</p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li>Step 1: With your hand extended flat, wrap the measuring tape loosely around your palm at the knuckles.</li>
                <li>Step 2: With the measuring tape around your knuckles, make a fist with your hand.</li>
                <li>Step 3: Loosen or tighten your fist to match how you prefer your gloves to fit (looser for a roomier fit, tighter for a snugger fit).</li>
                <li>Step 4: Record the circumference measurement in inches. Match it to the size chart below.</li>
            </ul>
