            <p class="ceg-b32"><strong>What are the different types of men&rsquo;s gloves?</strong> Men&rsquo;s gloves come in a variety of different types including:</p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
	            <li><p><strong>LEATHER GLOVES</strong><br>There are gloves and then there are leather gloves; warmth has never been so sophisticated. Go for leather pairs with slight stretch for a comfortable fit. Macy&rsquo;s offers genuine leather and faux leather options as well. A durable pair is the perfect choice to match an outfit you&rsquo;d wear to work or to a special event.</p></li>
				<li><p><strong>KNIT GLOVES</strong><br>Turn up the cozy to the max with a pair of knit gloves. Knit gloves are typically made of ultra-soft and warm materials so they feel great on the hands. If you&rsquo;re looking for a flexible fit that doesn&rsquo;t feel restrictive, then you&rsquo;re looking in the right place.</p></li>
				<li><p><strong>WOOL &amp; WOOL BLEND GLOVES</strong><br>Wool and wool blends are insulated which help retain your body heat. If you&rsquo;re looking for something classic, then a pair of wool or wool blend gloves will fit the bill.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>TECH GLOVES</strong><br>Stay connected with a pair of tech gloves. Compatible with the latest touchscreen cell phones, tech gloves are a great addition to your daily commute during the colder months. Check your email, answer a call or send a text message without ever having to remove your gloves. Fingerless gloves are another way to access your phone while on the go without sacrificing warmth.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>ACTIVE GLOVES</strong><br>Take training up a notch with a pair of active gloves. Lightweight and flexible, active gloves help strengthen your grip while lifting weights at the gym. Embrace the extra padding to help protect your hands. Utilize active gloves with adjustable closures for a secure fit.</p></li>
